The course provides an overview of the principles of internship supervision in the field of medical sciences and the role of an internship supervisor. Students instruct undergraduate students related with the courses like "Therapeutic exercise" and "Physiotherapy assessment". The development of study skills is supported by the planning of work related to the supervision of the student's internship, analysis and interpretation of professional experience, communication skills, time planning skills, the ability to give both oral and written feedback, and self-analysis. The course supports the assessment and development of tasks related to the supervision of trainees during the student's future career.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to provide students with experience in supervising physiotherapy process.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. knows the principles of internship supervision in the field of medical sciences and the role of the supervisor in the process of supervision 2. will have the experience to supervise in the context of therapeutic exercise and physiotherapy assessment 3. reflects his own actions as supervisor 4. analyses the quality of actions of supervised person
